                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" source="#bib2469-2" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons">Bishop of Antioch who was deprived of his see Synod of Antioch because of
                        heretical teachings</note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:lang="en" corresp="http://syriaca.org/johnofephesus http://syriaca.org/johnofephesus/persons">
                        <quote source="#bib2469-7">Paul was a bishop of Antioch in the 260s and a controversial theologian. He taught that Jesus had been born a mere man and been infused with the divine spirit only at his baptism. Denying the innate divine nature of Jesus, he was later framed as a precursor of Arianism and Nestorianism and condemned as a heretic.</quote>
                    </note>
